This paper deals with the problem of identifying duplicate GitHub repositories, which is a topic related to software engineering (cs.SE). The authors use various metrics and machine learning techniques to identify related repositories, which involves information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG). They also use graph theory to create a denoised graph of related repositories, which involves database systems (cs.DB) and complex systems (cs.CY).
